{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YUbjURE33GWoKnhVNahbZz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GDT2hwcZzHfCTdKczn2YZv","name":"Grep","input":{"pattern":"Decision 6|Epic Completion|epic_flow|Epic State Transition","path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md","output_mode":"content","-C":5,"head_limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4816,"cache_read_input_tokens":51433,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4816,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016EMr5poT3LRabJonL53yHn","session_id":"d383a9e0-3bc4-4a94-aaff-6965a5cc223b","uuid":"314d1a5e-55a9-43a7-8217-c08b3702e1cc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GDT2hwcZzHfCTdKczn2YZv","type":"tool_result","content":"63-src/lib/\n64-├── worktree-manager.ts       # NEW — git worktree create/merge/cleanup lifecycle\n65-├── lane-pool.ts              # NEW — manages concurrent lanes, scheduling\n66-├── merge-agent.ts            # NEW — dispatches dev agent for conflict resolution\n67-├── telemetry-writer.ts       # NEW — NDJSON append for per-story telemetry\n68:├── hierarchical-flow.ts      # NEW — parses story_flow/epic_flow/execution from YAML\n69:├── epic-completion.ts        # NEW — detects all-stories-done, triggers epic_flow\n70-\n71-src/lib/ink-lane.tsx          # NEW — Lane component (per-epic workflow view)\n72-src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx # NEW — LaneContainer (side-by-side layout)\n73-src/lib/ink-summary-bar.tsx   # NEW — SummaryBar (done/merging/pending)\n74-src/lib/ink-merge-status.tsx  # NEW — MergeStatus (conflict resolution display)\n75-src/lib/ink-collapsed-lanes.tsx # NEW — CollapsedLanes (one-line summaries)\n76-\n77-src/schemas/\n78:├── workflow.schema.json      # MODIFY — add execution, story_flow, epic_flow sections\n79-├── telemetry.schema.json     # NEW — NDJSON entry schema\n80-```\n81-\n82-## Core Architectural Decisions\n83-\n--\n199-\n200-**Rationale:** Serialized merges prevent race conditions on main. The merge agent gets full semantic context, not just diff markers. 3 attempts is generous — most conflicts are additive (different functions in same file).\n201-\n202-### Decision 4: Hierarchical Flow Model\n203-\n204:**Decision:** Workflow YAML gains three sections: `execution` (sprint-level config), `story_flow` (per-story pipeline), `epic_flow` (per-epic completion tasks). The existing flat `flow:` is syntactic sugar for `story_flow:` with `execution: { max_parallel: 1 }`.\n205-\n206-**Schema:**\n207-```yaml\n208-execution:\n209-  max_parallel: 2\n--\n225-  - loop:\n226-      - retry\n227-      - verify\n228-  - telemetry\n229-\n230:epic_flow:\n231-  - retro\n232-  - merge       # built-in\n233-  - validate    # built-in\n234-```\n235-\n236:**Backward compatibility:** If only `flow:` is present (no `story_flow`/`epic_flow`/`execution`), the engine treats it as `story_flow: <flow>` with `execution: { max_parallel: 1, epic_strategy: sequential }`. Zero behavior change for existing workflows.\n237-\n238:**Built-in tasks:** `merge` and `validate` are engine-handled (like `agent: null`). They don't appear in `tasks:` — the engine recognizes them as built-in epic_flow steps.\n239-\n240-**Rationale:** Three-level hierarchy maps naturally to sprint → epic → story. Backward compatibility means existing workflows work unchanged. Built-in merge/validate avoids forcing users to define agent configs for git operations.\n241-\n242-### Decision 5: Engine-Handled Null Tasks\n243-\n--\n277-}\n278-```\n279-\n280-**Rationale:** Null tasks are pure data operations — no LLM needed. The handler registry is extensible. New built-in tasks just add a handler function.\n281-\n282:### Decision 6: Epic Completion Detection\n283-\n284:**Decision:** The engine tracks per-epic story counts. When all stories in an epic reach `done`, the engine triggers `epic_flow` tasks in sequence.\n285-\n286-**Detection logic:**\n287-```typescript\n288-function checkEpicCompletion(state: SprintState, epicId: string): boolean {\n289-  const epicStories = getStoriesForEpic(state, epicId);\n--\n291-}\n292-```\n293-\n294-**Epic state transitions:**\n295-- `backlog` → `in-progress`: when lane is created for this epic\n296:- `in-progress` → `completing`: when all stories done, epic_flow starts\n297:- `completing` → `merging`: epic_flow reaches merge step\n298-- `merging` → `validating`: merge succeeded, running tests\n299-- `validating` → `done`: tests passed, worktree cleaned\n300-- `validating` → `failed`: tests failed after 3 merge agent attempts\n301-\n302-**Rationale:** Epic completion is deterministic — just count done stories. The multi-step completion state (completing → merging → validating → done) gives the TUI and status command precise information about where the epic is in its lifecycle.\n--\n408-src/lib/\n409-├── worktree-manager.ts       # Git worktree lifecycle (create/merge/cleanup)\n410-├── lane-pool.ts              # Lane scheduling, Promise.race loop\n411-├── merge-agent.ts            # Conflict resolution dispatch\n412-├── telemetry-writer.ts       # NDJSON append\n413:├── hierarchical-flow.ts      # Parse execution/story_flow/epic_flow\n414-├── epic-completion.ts        # All-stories-done detection\n415-├── ink-lane.tsx              # Lane component\n416-├── ink-lane-container.tsx    # Layout manager (side-by-side/stacked/single)\n417-├── ink-summary-bar.tsx       # Done/merging/pending bar\n418-├── ink-merge-status.tsx      # Merge progress display\n419-├── ink-collapsed-lanes.tsx   # One-line lane summaries\n420-\n421-src/schemas/\n422:├── workflow.schema.json      # MODIFY: execution, story_flow, epic_flow\n423-├── telemetry.schema.json     # NEW: NDJSON entry schema\n424-\n425-test/\n426-├── unit/\n\n[Showing results with pagination = limit: 100]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016EMr5poT3LRabJonL53yHn","session_id":"d383a9e0-3bc4-4a94-aaff-6965a5cc223b","uuid":"488f7990-a46c-41d4-92c2-d9957256b2e2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:14:44.202Z"}
