onMs`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 9: `EpicFlowConfig` includes all required fields\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ EpicFlowConfig > accepts all required fields\n✓ EpicFlowConfig > accepts optional dispatchRetro callback\n✓ EpicFlowConfig > accepts rebase merge strategy\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Interface at lines 24-45 defines: `epicId`, `epicFlow`, `worktreeManager`, `mergeStrategy`, `testCommand`, `projectDir`, `initialState`, `onConflict?`, `dispatchRetro?`, `onStateChange?`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 10: Lane is freed after epic flow completes\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ lane freed after completion > returns a resolved promise (no hanging) on success\n✓ lane freed after completion > returns a resolved promise (no hanging) on failure\n```\n\n---\n\n## AC 11: Empty `epicFlow` returns success immediately, transitions to `done`\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ empty epicFlow > returns success immediately with empty stepsCompleted\n✓ empty epicFlow > transitions epic through merging → validating → done\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Lines 178-192 handle empty flow fast-path through `EMPTY_FLOW_TRANSITIONS: ['merging', 'validating', 'done']`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 12: Worktree cleanup happens via `mergeWorktree` (not separately)\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ merge step > worktree cleanup happens via mergeWorktree (not separately)\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** No separate `cleanupWorktree` call exists in `epic-flow-executor.ts`. The merge step at lines 127-132 only calls `mergeWorktree`, which handles cleanup internally.\n\n---\n\n## Full Flow Integration Tests\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n```\n✓ full flow integration > executes retro → merge → validate and transitions through all states\n✓ full flow integration > retro failure prevents merge and validate from running\n✓ full flow integration > merge failure prevents validate from running\n✓ full flow integration > validate failure after merge success\n```\n\n---\n\n#