e failure prevents validate from running","-✓ full flow integration > validate failure after merge success","-```"," ","----","+No separate cleanupWorktree call — cleanup happens inside mergeWorktree (story 18-1)."," "," ## Summary"," ","-| AC | Description | Result |","-|----|-------------|--------|","-| 1  | Module exports | PASS |","-| 2  | Sequential execution | PASS |","-| 3  | Retro step | PASS |","-| 4  | Merge step | PASS |","-| 5  | Validate step | PASS |","-| 6  | State transitions | PASS |","-| 7  | Failure handling | PASS |","-| 8  | EpicFlowResult fields | PASS |","-| 9  | EpicFlowConfig fields | PASS |","-| 10 | Lane freed | PASS |","-| 11 | Empty epicFlow | PASS |","-| 12 | Worktree cleanup via merge | PASS |","+| AC | Result |","+|----|--------|","+| 1  | PASS |","+| 2  | PASS |","+| 3  | PASS |","+| 4  | PASS |","+| 5  | PASS |","+| 6  | PASS |","+| 7  | PASS |","+| 8  | PASS |","+| 9  | PASS |","+| 10 | PASS |","+| 11 | PASS |","+| 12 | PASS |"," "," **Final Result: ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs)**","-","-**Tests for this story: 38 tests, all passing**","+**Tests: 38 passed, 0 failed**"," **Coverage: 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines**"]}],"originalFile":"# Verification Proof: Story 19.2 — Epic Flow Execution\n\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (local CLI checks, test-provable tier)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n**Environment:** Local macOS (darwin), Node.js, npm\n**CLI Version:** codeharness 0.26.6\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: Build\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n```output\n> codeharness@0.26.6 build\n> tsup\nESM dist/index.js 423.98 KB\nESM ⚡️ Build success in 29ms\nDTS ⚡️ Build success in 899ms\n```\n\nZero errors, zero warnings from build.\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Tests\n\n**Result: PASS (5015 passed, 0 failed)**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run\n```\n\n```output\nTest Files  184 passed (184)\nTests       5015 passed (5015)\n```\n\nAll 184 test files pass. Zero failures.\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: Linter\n\n**Result: PASS (with warnings)**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\n\n```output\n✖ 66 problems (8 errors, 58 warnings)\n```\n\nNote: The 8 errors and 58 warnings are pre-existing across the codebase (timeout.ts, formatters.ts, verify/index.ts, etc.) — none are in `epic-flow-executor.ts` or its test file.\n\n---\n\n## Step 4: Coverage\n\n**Result: PASS — epic-flow-executor.ts: 100% Stmts, 100% Branch, 100% Funcs, 100% Lines**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run --coverage\n```\n\n```output\n...w-executor.ts |     100 |      100 |     100 |     100 |\n...completion.ts |     100 |      100 |     100 |     100 |\nAll files        |   96.76 |    88.54 |   98.36 |   97.37 |\n```\n\n---\n\n## AC 1: Module exports `executeEpicFlow`, `EpicFlowConfig`, `EpicFlowResult`, `EpicFlowStepResult`\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — File exists:**\n```bash\nls -la src/lib/epic-flow-executor.ts\n```\n```output\n-rw-r--r--@ 1 ivintik  staff  7701 Apr  4 03:28 src/lib/epic-flow-executor.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence — Exports:**\n```\nexport interface EpicFlowConfig {          (line 24)\nexport interface EpicFlowStepResult {      (line 50)\nexport interface EpicFlowResult {          (line 64)\nexport class EpicFlowError extends Error { (line 86)\nexport async function executeEpicFlow(config: EpicFlowConfig): Promise<EpicFlowResult> { (line 169)\n```\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ exports > exports executeEpicFlow function\n✓ exports > exports EpicFlowError class\n```\n\n---\n\n## AC 2: Steps execute in strict sequence (retro → merge → validate), never in parallel\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ sequential execution > executes retro → merge → validate in strict sequence\n✓ sequential execution > never runs steps in parallel\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** `for (const step of config.epicFlow)` loop at line 194 — sequential iteration, `await` on each step.\n\n---\n\n## AC 3: `retro` step reads telemetry and dispatches analyst agent\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ retro step > reads telemetry and dispatches callback\n✓ retro step > succeeds without callback (retro is advisory)\n✓ retro step > passes empty telemetry array when no entries exist\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Lines 119-125 call `readTelemetryForEpic(config.epicId, config.projectDir)` and `config.dispatchRetro(config.epicId, telemetry)`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 4: `merge` step calls `worktreeManager.mergeWorktree`\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ merge step > calls worktreeManager.mergeWorktree with correct args\n✓ merge step > fails when mergeWorktree returns success: false with conflict\n✓ merge step > fails when mergeWorktree returns success: false with tests-failed\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Lines 127-132 call `config.worktreeManager.mergeWorktree(config.epicId, config.mergeStrategy, config.testCommand, config.onConflict)`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 5: `validate` step calls `validateMerge` from `cross-worktree-validator.ts`\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ validate step > calls validateMerge with correct args\n✓ validate step > fails when validation returns valid: false\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Lines 139-144 call `validateMerge({ testCommand, cwd, epicId, writeTelemetry: true })`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 6: Epic state transitions at each step boundary\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ state transitions > transitions completing → merging before merge step\n✓ state transitions > transitions merging → validating before validate step\n✓ state transitions > transitions to done after all steps succeed\n✓ state transitions > does not transition state for retro step (no mapping)\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** `STEP_STATE_MAP` at lines 99-102: `merge → merging`, `validate → validating`. Transition to `done` at line 240.\n\n---\n\n## AC 7: Step failure skips remaining steps and transitions to `failed`\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ failure handling > skips remaining steps on failure\n✓ failure handling > transitions to failed on step failure\n✓ failure handling > handles unknown step name as failure\n✓ failure handling > handles non-Error throw from a step (string coercion)\n✓ failure handling > includes \"unknown\" reason when merge fails without a reason field\n✓ failure handling > handles dispatchRetro throwing an error\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Lines 213-236 catch errors, transition to `failed`, return early.\n\n---\n\n## AC 8: `EpicFlowResult` includes all required fields\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ EpicFlowResult > has all expected fields on success\n✓ EpicFlowResult > has all expected fields on failure\n✓ EpicFlowResult > stepResults contain step name, success, and durationMs\n✓ EpicFlowResult > failed step result includes error string\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Interface at lines 64-79 defines: `success`, `epicId`, `stepsCompleted`, `stepResults`, `failedStep`, `error`, `durationMs`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 9: `EpicFlowConfig` includes all required fields\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ EpicFlowConfig > accepts all required fields\n✓ EpicFlowConfig > accepts optional dispatchRetro callback\n✓ EpicFlowConfig > accepts rebase merge strategy\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Interface at lines 24-45 defines: `epicId`, `epicFlow`, `worktreeManager`, `mergeStrategy`, `testCommand`, `projectDir`, `initialState`, `onConflict?`, `dispatchRetro?`, `onStateChange?`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 10: Lane is freed after epic flow completes\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ lane freed after completion > returns a resolved promise (no hanging) on success\n✓ lane freed after completion > returns a resolved promise (no hanging) on failure\n```\n\n---\n\n## AC 11: Empty `epicFlow` returns success immediately, transitions to `done`\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ empty epicFlow > returns success immediately with empty stepsCompleted\n✓ empty epicFlow > transitions epic through merging → validating → done\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** Lines 178-192 handle empty flow fast-path through `EMPTY_FLOW_TRANSITIONS: ['merging', 'validating', 'done']`.\n\n---\n\n## AC 12: Worktree cleanup happens via `mergeWorktree` (not separately)\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n**Evidence — Test:**\n```\n✓ merge step > worktree cleanup happens via mergeWorktree (not separately)\n```\n\n**Evidence — Code:** No separate `cleanupWorktree` call exists in `epic-flow-executor.ts`. The merge step at lines 127-132 only calls `mergeWorktree`, which handles cleanup internally.\n\n---\n\n## Full Flow Integration Tests\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n```\n✓ full flow integration > executes retro → merge → validate and transitions through all states\n✓ full flow integration > retro failure prevents merge and validate from running\n✓ full flow integration > merge failure prevents validate from running\n✓ full flow integration > validate failure after merge success\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| 1  | Module exports | PASS |\n| 2  | Sequential execution | PASS |\n| 3  | Retro step | PASS |\n| 4  | Merge step | PASS |\n| 5  | Validate step | PASS |\n| 6  | State transitions | PASS |\n| 7  | Failure handling | PASS |\n| 8  | EpicFlowResult fields | PASS |\n| 9  | EpicFlowConfig fields | PASS |\n| 10 | Lane freed | PASS |\n| 11 | Empty epicFlow | PASS |\n| 12 | Worktree cleanup via merge | PASS |\n\n**Final Result: ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs)**\n\n**Tests for this story: 38 tests, all passing**\n**Coverage: 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines**\n"}}
